In this article, the First Lady, Jill Biden, announces the passing of former First Lady Rosalynn Carter and asks for prayers for the Carter family. She also acknowledges the sacrifices made by military families, particularly those with loved ones deployed or stationed far away. The First Lady mentions her Joining Forces initiative, which supports military and veterans' spouses, caregivers, and survivors. Navy veteran and Norfolk Navy spouse, Sibrina Sears, speaks about the importance of events like Friendsgiving in bringing the military community together. President Joe Biden then addresses the audience, expressing gratitude for the military and their families. He shares personal experiences and emphasizes the importance of supporting those who serve. The President interacts with children in the audience and concludes by wishing everyone a Happy Thanksgiving.